      <div class="msgContentFrame">My question is:  What was wrong with experience points?  In FFXI or any RGP or MMO for that matter, you could pretty much count on consistent xp based on the mob's level.  In FFXI, fight an IT, get ~200 xp.  It should be the same here.  Also, every member of every party should get equal xp as everyone else.  One person getting 500 sp and another getting 50 is beyond retarded, stupid, and all things terrible.   <br /> <br />I would guess their reasoning is to prevent AFK leveling, but different jobs do different things, so its impossible to completely balance.  They need to get off their high-horse and stop obsessing over cheating.  People are going to cheat if there's even a small opportunity and powerlevel themselves.  It's no different than botting, powerleveling, goblin pet leveling, or astral burning in FFXI.  I don't condone cheating obviously, but you can bet that I won't be leveling my CON (or any job) unless its consistent and therefore not a waste of time.  </div>
